    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`'mousescroll'` is not respected.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nvim --clean`\n- `:set mousescroll=ver:1,hor:1`\n- Open the dialog pager (for example, with `z=`)\n- Scroll with the mouse.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`'mousescroll'` is respected.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-2961+ge84076c7c6",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "There's no discerning mousewheel scrolling from arrow presses in the vim.on_key() handler that implements this. So we could do this but that would mean a key arrow press would also scroll with the 'mousescroll' amount. I guess that would be fine:\n```diff\n--- a/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2/messages.lua\n@@ -558,10 +564,11 @@ local dialog_on_key = function(_, typed)\n   -- TODO: no hint anymore, so should at least be documented at some point.\n-  local map, eob = {}, typed:match('PageDown')\n+  local map, eob, scroll = {}, typed:match('PageDown'), o.mousescroll:match('ver:([0-9]*)')\n+  local up, down = 'H' .. scroll .. 'k', 'L' .. scroll .. 'j'\n   map['<Home>'], map['<End>'] = 'gg', 'G'\n-  map['<Up>'], map['<C-Y>'] = 'Hk', 'Hk'\n-  map['<Down>'], map['<C-E>'] = 'Lj', 'Lj'\n+  map['<Up>'], map['<C-Y>'] = up, up\n+  map['<Down>'], map['<C-E>'] = down, down\n ```\n",
            "created_at": "2026-04-17T22:16:36Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39172#issuecomment-4271640570",
            "id": 4271640570,
